OL,5, The total carbon footprint of the      
OL,6, richest 1% will grow while that of the 
OL,7, poorest 50% stays small, a study says. 
OL,9,FEmissions of the wealthiest are on     
OL,10,Ftrack to be 30 times higher than what's
OL,11,Fneeded to stop the planet from warming 
OL,12,Fabove 1.5C, according to the study.    
OL,14,FThe poorest 50%, however, will be most 
OL,15,Fseverely impacted by climate change.   
OL,17,FThe research, carried out by two       
OL,18,FEuropean environmental agencies, comes 
OL,19,Fas world leaders meet at the COP26     
OL,20,Fclimate conference in Glasgow.         
